snippet.textDisplay:
By far the best cover one can do and utmost justice done.... All those rants and hatred towards this version of the song i genuinely don't feel is legit.... The song was awesome to the core... I LISTEN TO  IT 10 TIMES A DAY ON REPEAT...  

Ali noor I've been following him since he did his "saari raat-noori" wayy back in coke studio.. And he's a really very very great singer to be very honest.. His voice is so goddamn awesome... So much breath Oriented rusty voice.. And that's the uniqueness of noori... If i may! 

Rahat saab to bhagwaan hai..meri aukhaad nai hai unke baare me kuch bhi keheneki..

But to specifically to point it OUT... The last part always gets me  goosebumps all over my body and  mainly it gets me TEARY.. it's like - I WANT THIS SONG THIS STORY TO CONTINUE AND NOT END BUT "THE END IS INEVITABLE" KINDA TONE.. ... i wait for that ending part very eagerly every time I listen.. 


THE SONG IS ONE OF THE BEST OF ALL COKE STUDIO SONGS... PEACEOUT ✌️

snippet.textDisplay: Truth be told when I heard this for the first time I didnt really like it so much I thought it was ok but the song literally grows on you and now after listening it for the 10th time I am just loving it. They have breathed new life to this legendary song. This version will go on to live forever  and will be appreciated a lot in the times to come. What set this song apart is the amazing guitar solo by Salman. Rahat and Noor were brilliant too. Original version was raw and wild this one is more measured and has its own magnetism. Kudos to the team especially Salma ahmad. Loving each and every second of it.. Thank you Salman, Rahat and Ali Noor for taking out time and putting so much effort. Kudos team.
